Klangphonics are a trio that produce and perform live electronic music. By using a combination of electronic elements and acoustic instruments, they bridge the gap between producer and live band. 
This results in a very natural, organic sound, whilst still retaining the energy associated with deep house and melodic techno.

Onstage drums, guitar and diverse percussion are blended with synths and sequencers, creating a performance that works as well in a club as it does in concert.

AURORA - A Soul With No King. An exclusive live performance for Vevo. 

Four albums into a heralded career, with keenly respected soundtrack work also part of her resume, AURORA is the kind of artist who stands her ground while still pleasing an ever-growing audience that discovers her music each year. Well known for "Runaway," "Cure For The Unknown," and "Cure For Me," The Norwegian pop singer has revealed plenty to us through the years. She was in her mid-teens when she shared her 'All My Demons Greet Me As A Friend' debut. Now, at 27, there's a bit more philosophy and a lot more refinement to her work. The songs she's shared from her upcoming 'What Happened To The Heart' (arriving June 7), feel light, but hit heavy. "Your Blood" and "The Conflict Of The Mind" probe into their subjects, ask questions, don't sit still. Now this "A Soul With No King" performance makes all that gravitas more palpable. Watchin
